# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# agentickit todo example — environment template
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Set any ONE of the keys below and the handler auto-detects which provider
# to use. Priority order (first hit wins): GROQ_API_KEY, OPENROUTER_API_KEY,
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, OPENAI_API_KEY, GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY,
# MISTRAL_API_KEY, AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY. Every mapped default model supports
# tool calling, so the todo actions work without further tweaking.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Free tier, no credit card ---------------------------------------------
# Groq has a generous free tier and the fastest inference API — highest
# auto-detect priority. Grab a key at https://console.groq.com/keys.
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...

# OpenRouter also has a free tier (no credit card). The auto-detected default
# is `openrouter/qwen/qwen3-coder:free`, which supports tool calling.
# Grab a key at https://openrouter.ai/keys.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...

# --- Alternative: direct provider keys --------------------------------------
# Uncomment the one you want to use. Credit card required for OpenAI,
# Anthropic, Google, and Mistral.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# GOOGLE_GENERATIVE_AI_API_KEY=...
# MISTRAL_API_KEY=...

# --- Alternative: Vercel AI Gateway -----------------------------------------
# Works with any prefix (openai/*, anthropic/*, groq/*, etc.). On Vercel
# deployments VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN is injected automatically.
# AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY=...

# --- Alternative: local vLLM via OpenAI Responses API -----------------------
# Run any OpenAI-compatible server (e.g. the sibling vllm-gpt project serving
# `openai/gpt-oss-20b` on a local GPU). Point OPENAI_BASE_URL at its `/v1`
# root and set OPENAI_API_KEY to any non-empty string. Then pin the model
# explicitly in `app/api/pilot/route.ts` (e.g. `model: "openai/gpt-oss-20b"`)
# so auto-detect doesn't substitute gpt-4o-mini, which the local server
# almost certainly does not host.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=dummy-value
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8000/v1
